Limpopo police have launched a manhunt for a 33-year-old man who allegedly killed his 6-year-old son in a village outside Seshego. Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said the 33-year-old man was alone at home with the boy while the mother was in Pretoria. He said there had allegedly been a heated telephonic argument between the parents. Mojapelo said the man allegedly killed the boy with a sharp object and fled the scene. Relatives discovered the young boyâ€™s body with a suicide note in the bedroom. The incident happened on Sunday. A case of murder has been opened. Police have urged Norman Semenya to report to the nearest police station.